title: Mets-Cubs NLCS Game 1 starting lineups: Lucas Duda out, Michael Cuddyer in at first
text:
advertisement | advertise on newsday 
The Mets are changing up a few things against the Chicago Cubs for Game 1 of the National League Championship Series after surviving a five-game set against the Dodgers. 
Everyday first baseman Lucas Duda is out of the starting lineup for the series opener with Michael Cuddyer getting a shot against Cubs lefty Jon Lester. Latest Mets stories
